&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The spec has changed so that the result of enumerateDevices is cached
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; in a browsing session and never updated by device changes unless the user
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; has permission.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Therefore, a page without device permissions can no longer poll
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; enumerateDevices to detect device changes.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; We can modify Chromium's implementation of both enumerateDevices and
